       #include <stdlib.h>

       int ttyslot (void);

DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       ttyslot  returns  the index of the current user's entry in
       the /var/adm/utmp file.   The  returned  index  is  accom-
       plished by scanning files in /dev for the name of the ter-
       minal associated with the  standard  input,  the  standard
       output, or the standard error output (0, 1, or 2).

   FFiilleess
       /var/adm/utmp

   EErrrroorrss
       A  value  of  -1  is  returned if an error was encountered
       while searching for the terminal name or if  none  of  the
       above  file  descriptors  are  associated  with a terminal
       device.

